      "description": "Presenting a collector-grade 2002 BMW M3 (E46) that defines mechanical perfection. This specimen is powered by the iconic S54 3.2L straight-six engine, featuring individual throttle bodies and a double-VANOS variable valve timing system that has been meticulously serviced for optimal torque delivery. The drivetrain is anchored by a precise Getrag six-speed manual transmission and a variable M differential lock. Critical enthusiast concerns have been addressed: the rear subframe is professionally reinforced, and the rod bearings have been replaced as preventative maintenance. The chassis maintains its factory-spec suspension geometry with zero bushing deflection, while the undercarriage remains completely dry. This is a turn-key, high-revving masterpiece for the purist who demands uncompromised performance and structural integrity.",
